OL,3,CHarry Potter book first bought for
OL,4,C#3.50 by Birmingham woman sold for
OL,5,C#6,600
OL,7,FA rare copy of a Harry Potter book has
OL,8,Fsold for thousands at auction, 27
OL,9,Fyears after its owner bought it brand
OL,10,Fnew for a few pounds.
OL,12,FThe soft cover first edition of 'Harry
OL,13,FPotter and the Philosopher's Stone'
OL,14,Fwent under the hammer today at Richard
OL,15,FWinterton Auctioneers in Staffordshire
OL,16,Fand sold for #6,600, and will rise to
OL,17,F#8,000 with fees.
OL,19,FJane Thompson-Webb, from Erdington,
OL,20,Fbought the book brand new in 1997 from
OL,21,FOttakar's Bookshop in Birmingham.
