OL,7,FShe was working there at the time, and
OL,8,Fwith her staff discount ended up
OL,9,Fpaying #3.50 for it instead of the
OL,10,Frecommended retail price.
OL,12,FThe book sat on Jane's bookshelf for
OL,13,Fnearly 30 years until this afternoon
OL,14,Fwhen it was sold.
OL,16,FIn a statement, auctioneer Richard
OL,17,FWinterton said: "This is a fantastic
OL,18,Fresult and one of the highest prices
OL,19,Fachieved at auction, which reflects
OL,20,Fthe wonderful condition this copy is
OL,21,Fin.
